SIMPLE: tommy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tommy
<hw>Tom"my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Bread, --
generally a penny roll; the supply of food carried by workmen as their
daily allowance.</def> <mark>[Slang,Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A truck, or barter; the exchange of labor for goods,
not money.</def> <mark>[Slang, Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Tommy</xex> is used adjectively or in compounds;
as, <xex>tommy</xex> master,
<xex>tommy</xex>-store,<xex>tommy</xex>-shop,etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Same as <er>Tommy Atkins</er>; -- a shortened
form.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tommy Atkins</ent>⟦br⟧
